						<h2>About</h2>
				 		<a href="documents/cv_huang.pdf" target="_blank">Curriculum Vitae</a> | <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=0kTel90AAAAJ" target="_blank">Google Scholar</a> | <a href="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6838-3701" target="_blank">ORCiD</a> <br>
				 		My scientific work contributes to the fields of human-robot interaction (HRI), human-computer interaction (HCI), and robotics.
				 		The research directions I am currently pursuing include: 
						<ul>
				 			<li>Making robotic technology more accessible to people with diverse backgrounds.</li> 
				 			<li>Understanding the long-term effects of human-robot interactions in real-world settings.</li>
				 			<li>Improving the quality of life for older adults using technology.</li>
				 			<li>Designing effective interaction strategies for AI systems to assist people.</li>
				 		</ul>
				 		<!-- <br><br> -->
				 		My research has been supported by NSF, NIH, NIST, Johns Hopkins Institute for Assured Autonomy (IAA), Applied Physics Laboratory, and Malone Center for Engineering in Healthcare. 
